    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="witness" subtype="poem" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" rhyme="aa">
                <pb facs="MSIX35r"/>
                <space quantity="15" unit="lines"/>
                <lg type="stanza">
                    <l><handShift new="#HANDJR1833-34" script="cursive-copperplate" medium="ink"/>We have wound a weary way,<ref type="gloss_textual" target="andernacht_poem_glosses_textual.php#ANDERNACHTVERSIONGLOSS" /></l>
                    <l>Twilights mists are gathering grey,</l>
                    <l>Purple now the hills are showing</l>
                    <l>Bright the western clouds are glowing</l>
                    <l>Lashing on with giant force,</l>
                <pb facs="MSIX35v"/>
                    <l>Rolls the <placeName corresp="#RHINE">Rhine</placeName> his sullen course,</l>
                    <l>Flash his waves with flamy red,</l>
                    <l>Eddying oer their <name type="geological" corresp="#BASALT">basalt</name> bed,</l>
                    <l>Now with wide expanded breast</l>
                    <l>Now between the hills compressed,</l>
                    <l>Ever noble, ever free,</l>
                    <l>Flows his river majesty</l>
                    <l>Now upon the evening skies,</l>
                    <l><placeName corresp="#ANDERNACH">Andernacht</placeName>&#x02BC;s grey ruins rise,<ref type="gloss_contextual" target="andernacht_glosses_contextual.php#ANDERNACHTSGREYRUINSGLOSS"/></l>
                    <l>Memorials of the <placeName corresp="#ROMEANCIENT">Roman</placeName> power,<ref type="gloss_contextual" target="andernacht_glosses_contextual.php#ROMANPOWERGLOSS"/></l>
                    <l>Buttress and battlement and tower,</l>
                    <l>Decaying, falling fast away,</l>
                    <l>The monuments of <persName corresp="#JULIUSCAESAR">Caesar</persName>s sway,</l>
                    <l>In heaps together loosely thrown,</l>
                    <l>The sculptured head, inscriptioned stone</l>
                    <l>Unguarded now the bridges length,</l>
                    <l>And failing fast its arches strength</l>
                    <l>The green sod in the moat is growing</l>
                    <l>The cold wind in the chambers blowing</l>
                    <l>And flapping through the thin night air</l>
                    <l>The owl and bat the tenants there,</l>
                </lg>
            </div>
